Additionally, the paper addresses the challenge of Byzantine Fault Tolerance (BFT) in decentralized learning systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. The paper also discusses security and theoretical analysis, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The paper proposes a novel algorithm for achieving BFT, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of algorithms and theoretical analysis, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
